<subSubSection id="E3EA1CE3FF987C08FF2FF9C76B05F89C" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="AB4F4F68FF987C08FF2FF9C76B05F89C" blockId="4.[151,1437,1093,1875]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="9984937AFF987C08FF2FF9C76B7AF9B4" bold="true" box="[199,315,1633,1659]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="6CF034EBFF987C08FEADF9C76816F9B4" box="[325,599,1633,1659]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="knightiellus">
<emphasis id="9984937AFF987C08FEADF9C76816F9B4" box="[325,599,1633,1659]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">Hishimonus knightiellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was earlier described from Borneo, 
<collectingCountry id="D3E70FF8FF987C08FBE8F9C76E28F9B4" box="[1024,1129,1633,1659]" name="Malaysia" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="D3E70FF8FF987C08FB90F9C76EA9F9B4" box="[1144,1256,1633,1659]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="D3E70FF8FF987C08FACCF9C76F26F9B4" box="[1316,1383,1633,1659]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">China</collectingCountry>
(the 
<typeStatus id="744BF1CAFF987C08FF7FF9236A86F950" box="[151,199,1669,1695]" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">type</typeStatus>
was not examined in the present work). It is here recorded for the first time from 
<collectingCountry id="D3E70FF8FF987C08FB99F9236EEAF950" box="[1137,1195,1669,1695]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">India</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="6934818AFF987C08FB52F9236F5DF950" box="[1210,1308,1669,1695]" country="India" name="Haryana" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">Haryana</collectingRegion>
). It closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="6CF034EBFF987C08FEE7F90C68D3F90C" authority="Viraktamath &amp; Murthy" authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Anantha Murthy" authorityYear="2014" box="[271,658,1705,1731]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spicans">
<emphasis id="9984937AFF987C08FEE7F90C6BC7F90C" box="[271,390,1706,1731]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="135">H. spicans</emphasis>
Viraktamath &amp; Murthy
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished in having the pygofer lobe with many stout macrosetae over the dorsocaudal quarter; aedeagal basal processes not widely splayed, closer to each other than to shaft, about half as long as shaft, with blunt ends; and gonopore subapical on ventral margin (Figs 16 – 18). We provide photographic illustrations which complement the earlier descriptions given by Viraktamath and Anantha Murthy (2014).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
